🧾 What I did in this experiment

In this experiment, I deployed Jenkins inside Docker using Docker Compose. After starting Jenkins, I completed the initial setup and installed the HTML Publisher plugin. Then I created a Pipeline job called karunya-site-pipeline and pasted a Jenkins pipeline script. This script generated a simple static website for Karunya University by creating HTML and CSS files automatically during the build. After running the pipeline, Jenkins published the generated website inside the build page and archived the website files as build artifacts.

🎤 Viva explanation

I used Docker Compose to run Jenkins in a Docker container. Then I configured Jenkins and installed the HTML Publisher plugin. After that, I created a Pipeline job and added a Jenkins pipeline script to generate a static website. The pipeline generated HTML and CSS files, published the website inside Jenkins, and archived the files as artifacts for later viewing or download.

